snippet: Cardinal Timothy M. Dolan did not intend to question Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo’s standing in the Catholic Church, a spokesman said.
abstract: Spokesman for archbishop of New York, Cardinal Timothy M Dolan, says he did not intend to question Gov Andrew M Cuomo's standing in Roman Catholic church, despite governor's support for abortion rights; statement seeks to clarify comments cardinal made on radio about Cuomo.
lead_paragraph: Cardinal Timothy M. Dolan did not intend to question Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo’s standing in the Catholic Church, a spokesman said.

headline.seo: Cardinal Dolan Clarifies Remarks About Cuomo
